# ========================
# GLOBAL BEHAVIOR
# ========================
Follow the existing project architecture and coding style strictly.
Analyze existing code before generating new code.
Prefer consistency over creativity.

# ========================
# ARCHITECTURE RULES
# ========================
Respect Clean Architecture: data / domain / presentation layers.

- Do not mix layers.
- Presentation layer must not contain business logic.
- Domain layer must be independent (no Flutter imports).
- Data layer handles API, models, and repositories implementation.

Always use existing architecture patterns from the project.

# ========================
# FILE MODIFICATION RULES
# ========================
Only modify files explicitly mentioned in the request.

Do not:
- Modify unrelated files
- Refactor large parts of the project unless explicitly requested
- Move code between files without permission

# ========================
# REUSE & CONSISTENCY
# ========================
Always reuse existing:
- Models
- Repositories
- Services
- Utilities

Do not duplicate logic.
Search the project before creating new code.

# ========================
# NAMING & STYLE
# ========================
Follow the naming conventions used in the project.

- Keep functions small and readable
- Use clear and descriptive names
- Match formatting and structure of existing files

Do not introduce new patterns if similar ones already exist.

# ========================
# FILE CREATION RULES
# ========================
Do not create new files unless absolutely necessary.

If needed:
- Follow the existing folder structure
- Respect naming conventions

# ========================
# API & DATA HANDLING
# ========================
Use existing API clients (e.g., Dio setup).

- Do not create new HTTP clients
- Use existing interceptors and configurations
- Respect existing response models

# ========================
# STATE MANAGEMENT
# ========================
Follow the existing state management approach (Bloc / Cubit).

- Do not introduce new state management solutions
- Keep logic inside Bloc/Cubit, not UI

# ========================
# UI RULES
# ========================
Do not modify UI unless explicitly requested.

UI must:
- Remain clean
- Not contain business logic
- Use existing widgets/components when possible

# ========================
# SAFETY RULES
# ========================
Do not break existing functionality.

Avoid regressions:
- Do not remove existing logic
- Do not change method signatures without reason

# ========================
# OUTPUT QUALITY
# ========================
Generated code must be:
- Clean
- Maintainable
- Consistent with the project

If unsure:
- Ask for clarification instead of guessing